str2: From en and the base of trope; to invert, i.e. in a good sense, to respect; or in a bad one, to confound.

str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

str2: To admonish, warn, counsel, exhort. From the same as nouthesia; to put in mind, i.e. to caution or reprove gently.
Probably adverb of comparative from hos; which how, i.e. In that manner.

str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
A child, descendent, inhabitant. From the base of timoria; a child.
